      <bioghist id="aspace_531571c0ba9dc6a169270a9667e716e1">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Henry John May began the practice of law in Johannesburg in 1925 and was considered an authority on native law and customs. He wrote and lectured on apartheid, constitutional law, and South African history.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_6b8fc7b778a7baa123a24355fa04557d">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of an unpublished autobiography by former South African lawyer Henry John May. The memoir describes May's personal life as well as his professional career.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
